721265f-a.text:
Madison Avenue, east side, from 36th to 34th Streets, showing Madison Avenue entrance to B. Altman's store. This side of the Altman building is the newest constructed between 1910 and 1915.
About 1915.

721266f-a.text:
Madison Ave., east side, north from East 34th to 37th Streets, showing in the foreground a row of 4-story houses (Nos. 189-197) that will be replaced by a 14-story apartment house. On the N.E. corner of East 35th Street, appears the Church of the Incarnation. Occupying the 36th to
37th block is the J. P. Morgan home and Library.
September 1, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.

721267f-b.text:
197 to 185 Madison Ave., east side, south from East 35th to 34th Streets, showing a row of houses, Nos. 197 to 189, that will be demolished and the site improved by a 14-story apartment house, to be known as No. 20 East 35th Street. This new structure will occupy the entire upper portion of this block front exclusive of the N.E. corner of East 34th Street where upon stands the 16estory Cameron Building, No. 195. For further data see, the New York Times -- October 14, 1937, Page 46L.
September 15, 1937.
George D. Chinn.
